HEADWORD: Meuse
<hw>Meuse</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A European river,
flowing into the North Sea.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Meuse River.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An American operation in World War I (1918);
American troops under Pershing drove back the German armies which were
saved only by the Armistice on November 11.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Meuse River, Argonne, Argonne Forest, Meuse-Argonne,
Meuse-Argonne operation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meuse-Argonne</ent>⟦br⟧
